(firstQuint)Vaginal Compared With Intramuscular Progesterone for Prevention of Preterm Birth in High Risk Pregnant Women.

 The objectives of this study is 1) To compare the efficacy of two different regimens of progesterone therapy in preventing preterm birth less than 37 weeks of gestation.

 2) To compare the cost-benefit, adverse effects and patient preference of two different regimens of progesterone therapy.

 Design: Multi-center, randomized, open-label trial.

